                <div class="detail-box">
                  
                    <p style="text-align: justify; font-size:14px">
                         
Seva Hands flagship project, our Sandwich Drive, serves over 500 lunches a week to learners in the Reservoir Hills
and Clare Estate community. During the dark times of COVID we sustained our efforts and were buoyed by the testimony
of teachers that shared stories of guaranteed attendance on the days we supplied lunches. One sandwich can make a difference
- we have seen this for ourselves. The larger message through this time was the fact that we were not just providing a sandwich, 
we were steadfast in our support. Hope, faith and love came in the form of a sandwich.

                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="box" style="margin-top: -30px;">
                <div class="img-box">
                    <img src="~/images/middleseva-fotor.jpg" alt="" />
                </div>
                <div class="detail-box">
                  
                    <p style="text-align: justify; font-size:14px">
                        
                        Our annual Diwali Hamper Drive has been a staple of Seva Hands since 2019 and accompanying this annual
                        drive is the provision of ad-hoc hampers. As Seva Hands grew organically, our community faced a battery
                        of challenges and we geared ourselves to support them. The power of collective efforts saw us supporting 
                        those in need during COVID, the floods and riots. Being receptive to our community is what drives us as we
                        know the value of uplifting those in need when they are feeling the lowest.


                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="box" style="margin-top: -30px;">
                <div class="img-box">
                    <img src="~/images/helpedchild.png" alt="" />
                </div>
                <div class="detail-box">

                    <p style="text-align: justify;font-size:14px">

                        
                        Seva Hands also provides sandwiches to the local Senior Citizens while they are waiting for their pension payouts.
                        We maintain contact with the local Senior Citizens homes and Homes of Safety, assisting where we can. During the
                        school holidays we distribute the bread, we are fortunate enough to receive, to the various Homes and communities 
                        around us. We have witnessed the joy on the faces of those receiving the simplest of gifts and that fills our cups!


                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
