                            Seva Hands is a non-profit organisation that was established in 2019 by a group of friends. What brought us together  was our common desire to make a positive impact on our community. Our journey began with a simple goal of providing school lunches to learners in need in our local schools. We saw the link between the sustenance of a child, their succesful performance in school and the step change in the quality of the lives of each child AND their respective families.
                            The challenges of COVID illustrated the need to be receptive to the broader needs of our community and we actively rose to support these needs. The cornerstones of operating with absolute transparency and integrity, coupled with attaining all relevant certification, has seen our network grow and this feeds into our desire to grow our reach and positively impact upon more lives.

                        </p>
